S, TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Having long hair."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) ―         -b2-  A"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fleshy, plump,"},{"kind":"text","text":"boy. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAfiyapu All~aHomi","text_ar":"عَافِيَةُ اللَّحْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"A she-camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having much flesh:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAfiyaAtN","text_ar":"عَافِيَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroDN EaAfiyapN","text_ar":"اَرْضٌ عَافِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A land of which the herbage, not having been depastured, has become abundant."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Some broth that is returned in the cooking-pot when it has been borrowed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAfiY Alqidori","text_ar":"عَافِى القِدْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is left in the cooking-pot"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S, M)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by the borrower, for the lender."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EafowapN","text_ar":"عَفْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]       -A4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A guest:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * K:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any seeker,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"demander, of a favour"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bounty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of means of subsistence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEotaf","text_ar":"مُعْتَف","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EufaApN","text_ar":"عُفَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA)"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2095},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EufiY~u","text_ar":"عُفِىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, * K,) both signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"guests,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., (TA,) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAfiyapN","text_ar":"عَافِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, * TA;) which last signifies also beasts, and birds, (S, TA,) as well as men, (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seekers of,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seeking, the means of subsistence;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA;) and its pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EawaAfK","text_ar":"عَوَافٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa kaviyru AlEufaApi","text_ar":"هُوَ كَثِيرُ العُفَاةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaAfiyapi","text_ar":"العَافِيَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEufiY~i","text_ar":"العُفِىِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is one who has many guests,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (S, TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A seeker of herbage."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA. [In the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alz~Ay^idu","text_ar":"الزّايِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~aAy^idu","text_ar":"الرَّايِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A comer to water:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAfiyapu AlmaA='i","text_ar":"عَافِيَةُ المَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the comers to the water."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","As","S","M","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n31033","headword_ar":"عَافٌ","root":"Ewf","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saholN","text_ar":"سَهْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A soft tract,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a plain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (O, K.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]}}